==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aerie
<hw>Ae"rie</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>aire</ets>, <ets>eire</ets>, <ets>air</ets>, nest, also origin,
descent, OF. <ets>aire</ets>, LL. <ets>area</ets>, <ets>aera</ets>, nest
of a bird of prey, perh. fr. L. <ets>area</ets> an open space (for birds
of prey like to build their nests on flat and open spaces on the top of
high rocks). Cf. <er>Area</er>.]</ety> <def>The nest of a bird of prey,
as of an eagle or hawk; also a brood of such birds; eyrie.
<au>Shak.</au> Also fig.: A human residence or resting place perched
like an eagle's nest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>A⟦eum⟧riferous</ent>⟦br⟧
